post_summaries.description: The image is a close-up shot of pink blossoms on a tree branch. The blossoms are vibrant and fill the frame, with a soft, blurred background. Text overlayed on the image reads "Spring is a lovely reminder of how beautiful change can truly be." The Earthical Tribe logo is visible in the top left corner.

The image is a post from earthicaltribe.com.au on Instagram, listing various mental health support services in Australia, including Lifeline, Sane Australia, Beyond Blue, Suicide Call Back Service, Kids Helpline, Headspace, Parentline, MensLine Australia, Open Arms, Safe Steps, and OCD and Anxiety Helpline. The post also includes a caption discussing the impact of lockdowns and uncertainty on mental health, quoting a psychologist.
The image shows a person outdoors in an autumnal setting, reaching up towards a tree with golden leaves. They are wearing a dark outfit and carrying a tote bag with the word "VEGAN" printed on it.

The image is an Instagram post from earthicaltribe.com.au advertising their ethical vegan clothing. It features a couple wearing t-shirts and carrying tote bags with vegan-related slogans. The post also highlights the brand's commitment to no sweat shops, animal cruelty-free practices, and donating a portion of profits to animal rescue.
The image shows a tree with its leaves shaped like a heart, set in a field of green grass and small white flowers. The sky is visible in the background.

The image shows a sunny landscape with a green field and a blue sky with clouds. The text "2021 is on" is superimposed on the image. The post reflects on the challenges of 2020 and looks forward to 2021 with hope and a focus on resilience and gratitude.
